---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Controlled Evaluation | BeaconGuard Architecture Review"
  description="Request a bounded BeaconGuard Controlled Evaluation covering boundary placement, Compliance Playbook mapping, ALLOW and DENY cases, evidence review, and deployment fit."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Controlled Evaluation</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A Controlled Evaluation is a bounded architecture review for one regulated workflow. It validates Runtime Control Boundary placement, Compliance Playbook mapping, ALLOW and DENY cases, Verifiable Decision Records, and deployment fit without replacing existing systems of record.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Not a rip-and-replace proposal</h2>
    <p>
      Existing applications continue to own workflow logic and records. BeaconGuard is evaluated as a deterministic control and evidence boundary before governed execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Inputs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>One bounded workflow</li>
      <li>Representative request contract</li>
      <li>Required identity and trust context</li>
      <li>Desired controls for the Compliance Playbook</li>
      <li>Deployment assumptions</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Activities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Boundary placement review</li>
      <li>Request normalization and System Connector fit, when needed</li>
      <li>Compliance Playbook mapping</li>
      <li>ALLOW and DENY case design, including absent-approval DENY cases and trust failures</li>
      <li>Evidence review using Verifiable Decision Records</li>
      <li>Deployment-fit and responsibility review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Outputs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Architecture-fit memo</li>
      <li>Control responsibility matrix for the evaluated workflow</li>
      <li>Sample Compliance Playbook or mapping artifact</li>
      <li>Sample Verifiable Decision Records</li>
      <li>Blocker register</li>
      <li>Next-step recommendation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Who should participate</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--compact">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare</h3>
        <p>Teams owning PHI-sensitive operational AI pathways and privacy review obligations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial services</h3>
        <p>Teams owning AML, KYC, fraud, dispute, or customer-impacting recommendation workflows.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated internal automation</h3>
        <p>Teams placing agents or automations against production systems under fail-closed controls.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Contact the team</h2>
    <p>
      Timing and commercial terms are confirmed during intake. Do not submit PHI, customer records, credentials, production secrets, or confidential evidence in the initial message.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Request Controlled Evaluation</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/platform">Review platform overview</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
